result.execSummary:
The defendant Aaron J Danielski was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Aaron J Danielski is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Aaron J Danielski was found guilty of Sexual Contact with Child Age 15, Actor Under 19, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.093.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Aaron J Danielski in court. Attorney David E Saperstein in court for Aaron J Danielski.  Attorney Anthony Joseph Pozorski Sr. in court for State of Wisconsin. Per agreement, State moves to amend Cts 1 and 3 to 948.093 and will move to dismiss Ct 2. State will recommend 2 years probation with the following conditions: no contact with Victim #1, pay court costs, submit a DNA sample, participate in counseling that DOC deems appropriate, and to serve 30 days in jail for Ct 3. State opposes expungement. Court grants amendment to Cts 1 and 3. Court reviews plea questionnaire and finds defendant freely and knowingly waives rights. Defendant pleads no contest to Cts 1 and 3. Court accepts plea and finds defendant guilty of Cts 1 and 3 and Ct 2 dismiss per agreement. State heard. Attorney Saperstein heard. Defendant does not wish to be heard on sentencing. Court heard and orders 2 years probation for each count with the following conditions: no contact with Victim #1, to participate in counseling that DOC deems appropriate, to pay court costs, and to submit a DNA sample. Court grants expungement upon successful completion of probation.
